Privacy Policy for CapyVolley

Last updated: 3/8/2023

Introduction

Welcome to CapyVolley! This Privacy Policy explains how Visiorama LTDA ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and discloses information about you when you play CapyVolley (the "Game") and use our services related to the Game.

We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. By accessing or using the Game, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with this Privacy Policy, please do not use the Game.

Information Collection and Use

1. Information We Collect

(a) Information You Provide: When you play the Game or use certain features, we may collect information you provide directly to us. For example, when you create an account, we may collect your username, email address, and other profile information.

(b) Information We Automatically Collect: We may automatically collect certain information about your use of the Game. This information may include your device type, operating system, unique device identifiers, IP address, gameplay data, and other usage information.

(c) Location Information: The Game may collect precise location information from your device if you grant us permission to do so. We use this information to provide location-based features and services.

(d) Analytics and Advertising: We may use third-party analytics tools to analyze usage patterns in the Game. These tools collect information sent by your device, such as app usage and events. We may also show ads in the Game, and third-party ad networks may use cookies and similar technologies to collect information about your device and online activity to serve relevant ads.

2. Use of Information

(a) We use the information we collect to provide, maintain, and improve the Game, as well as to develop new features and services.

(b) We may use your email address to send you promotional communications, such as newsletters and special offers. You may opt-out of receiving these communications by following the instructions provided in the communication.

(c) We may use aggregated and de-identified information for any purpose, including to analyze usage patterns and improve the Game.

3. Sharing of Information

(a) We may share your information with third-party service providers that perform services on our behalf, such as hosting, analytics, and advertising services.

(b) We may share your information in response to a request for information if we believe disclosure is in accordance with any applicable law, regulation, or legal process.

(c) We may share your information to protect our rights, privacy, safety, or property, as well as those of our players or others.

(d) In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, your information may be transferred to the acquiring entity.

4. Your Choices

(a) Account Information: You may update or delete your account information at any time by contacting us at joaovicentedeconto@gmail.com.

(b) Location Information: You can disable location services in your device settings, but this may limit certain features of the Game.

(c) Cookies: Most web browsers are set to accept cookies by default. You can usually choose to set your browser to remove or reject browser cookies. If you choose to remove or reject cookies, this could affect the availability and functionality of the Game.

(d) Opt-Out: You may opt-out of receiving promotional communications from us by following the instructions provided in the communication.

5. Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is completely secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.

6. Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be effective when we post the revised Privacy Policy. Your continued use of the Game following the posting of changes means you accept those changes.

7. Contact Us

If you have any questions, comments, or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at joaovicentedeconto@gmail.com.

By playing CapyVolley, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described herein.
